<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Braille Translator - AutoDots</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        /* Apply Inter font globally and basic smoothing */
        body {
            font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
            -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
            -moz-osx-font-smoothing: grayscale;
        }
        /* Skip link specific styles */
        .skip-link {
            position: absolute;
            left: -10000px;
            top: auto;
            width: 1px;
            height: 1px;
            overflow: hidden;
        }
        .skip-link:focus {
            position: fixed; /* Fixed position for better visibility on focus */
            top: 10px;
            left: 10px;
            width: auto;
            height: auto;
            padding: 0.75em 1.25em;
            background-color: #2563eb; /* Tailwind's blue-600 */
            color: white;
            z-index: 9999; /* Ensure it's on top */
            border-radius: 0.375rem; /* Tailwind's rounded-md */
            text-decoration: none;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        /* Specific font stack for Braille characters */
        .braille-font {
            font-family: 'Apple Braille', 'Segoe UI Symbol', 'DejaVu Sans', ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Liberation Mono", "Courier New", monospace;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body class="font-sans bg-gray-100 text-gray-800 flex flex-col min-h-screen">
    <a href="#main-content" class="skip-link">Skip to main content</a>

    <header class="bg-white shadow-md sticky top-0 z-40">
        <nav class="container mx-auto px-6 py-4 flex justify-between items-center">
            <a href="/" class="text-3xl font-bold text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-700">AutoDots</a>
            <div class="space-x-1 sm:space-x-2 md:space-x-4">
                <a href="/" class="text-gray-700 hover:text-indigo-600 px-3 py-2 rounded-md text-sm sm:text-base font-medium">Home</a>
                <a href="/chat" class="text-indigo-600 bg-indigo-100 px-3 py-2 rounded-md text-sm sm:text-base font-medium" aria-current="page">Chat & Translate</a>
                <a href="/about" class="text-gray-700 hover:text-indigo-600 px-3 py-2 rounded-md text-sm sm:text-base font-medium">About</a>
                <a href="/supported-codes" class="text-gray-700 hover:text-indigo-600 px-3 py-2 rounded-md text-sm sm:text-base font-medium">Supported Codes</a>
            </div>
        </nav>
    </header>

    <main id="main-content" class="flex-grow container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8">
        <div class="w-full max-w-3xl mx-auto"> 
            <header class="mb-10 text-center">
                <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900">Braille Translator</h1>
            </header>

            <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 text-gray-700 p-6 mb-10 rounded-lg shadow-md" role="alert">
                <h2 class="font-bold text-2xl mb-3 text-blue-700">How to Use This Tool</h2>
                <p class="mb-3 text-lg">
                    This tool converts standard text, LaTeX expressions, or MathType content into Braille. 
                    The default translation is to <strong>Unified English Braille (UEB) Grade 1</strong>.
                </p>
                <strong class="block mb-2 text-lg">Instructions:</strong>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-1">
                    <li>Enter your plain text, LaTeX code, or MathType content into the text area below.</li>
                    <li>For <strong>MathType</strong>, please copy the expression directly from Microsoft Word. (Experimental support)</li>
                    <li>Click the "Translate" button.</li>
                    <li>The translated Braille output will appear below the form.</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mb-2">
                    <strong>For mathematical content (LaTeX):</strong> Please use standard LaTeX notation 
                    (e.g., <code class="bg-gray-200 text-gray-800 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-sm font-mono">\frac{a}{b}</code> for fractions, <code class="bg-gray-200 text-gray-800 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-sm font-mono">\sqrt{x}</code> for square roots). 
                    For more help, see the <a href="https://www.latex-project.org/help/documentation/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline">official LaTeX documentation</a> or <a href="https://www.overleaf.com/learn" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline">Overleaf's guides</a>.
                </p>
                <p class="text-sm italic text-blue-600">
                    Advanced features and other Braille grades may be processed differently based on input.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-6 sm:p-8 rounded-lg shadow-xl">
                <form method="post" action="/chat" class="space-y-6">
                    <div>
                        <label for="text" class="block text-lg font-medium text-gray-800 mb-2">Enter text, LaTeX, or MathType content:</label>
                        <textarea id="text" name="text" class="mt-1 block w-full rounded-lg border-gray-300 shadow-sm focus:border-indigo-500 focus:ring focus:ring-indigo-500 focus:ring-opacity-50 p-4 text-base h-48 resize-y">#if(inputText):#(inputText)#endif</textarea>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div>
                        <button type="submit" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center bg-indigo-600 text-white px-8 py-3 rounded-lg text-lg font-semibold hover:bg-indigo-700 transition-transform duration-150 ease-in-out focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-offset-2 focus:ring-indigo-500 shadow-md hover:shadow-lg active:bg-indigo-700">
                            <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2 -ml-1" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
                                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-8.707l-3-3a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414L10.586 9H7a1 1 0 100 2h3.586l-1.293 1.293a1 1 0 101.414 1.414l3-3a1 1 0 000-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                            </svg>
                            Translate
                        </button>
                    </div>
                </form>

                #if(output):
                    <div class="mt-10">
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Braille Output:</h2>
                        <pre class="braille-font bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 text-gray-800 whitespace-pre-wrap break-words overflow-x-auto shadow text-xl leading-relaxed">#(output)</pre>
                    </div>
                #endif

                #if(errorMessage):
                    <div class="mt-8 bg-red-100 border-l-4 border-red-500 text-red-700 p-4 rounded-md shadow" role="alert">
                        <strong class="font-bold">Error:</strong>
                        <span class="block sm:inline">#(errorMessage)</span>
                    </div>
                #endif
            </div>
        </div> 
    </main>

    <footer class="bg-gray-800 text-white text-center py-8 mt-auto">
        <div class="container mx-auto px-6">
            <p>&copy; 2025 AutoDots. All rights reserved.</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
                Providing accurate Braille translations for everyone.
            </p>
        </div>
    </footer>

</body>
</html>